  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its publication in 2020, \"Across Anthropology\" has yet to gain significant traction within academic circles, recorded with zero citations. However, its presence on commercial platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads indicates a potential interest that could be explored further.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Across Anthropology\" was published by Leuven University Press in 2020, yet it has not been cited in academic literature since its release. This lack of citations could suggest several factors, including niche interest levels within the academic community or relatively recent entry into the discourse surrounding anthropology.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of scholarly citations, the work is available on commercial platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, which points to a potential intersection between general readership and academic discourse. This presence might imply that the book has been recognized by a broader audience, although it has not yet yielded significant public discourse or engagement on platforms commonly associated with academic discussion.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The metrics also indicate a lack of mentions across social media and community platforms, suggesting that \"Across Anthropology\" has not sparked active debates or sustained public conversations in forums such as Reddit or Wikipedia. The absence of discussion on these platforms often correlates with a limited societal reach for scholarly works.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while \"Across Anthropology\" holds potential in terms of commercial interest, it has yet to firmly establish its scholarly significance or societal impact. Engaging with the academic community through discourse or even interdisciplinary connection might be avenues for enhancing its reach and relevance within both research and public spheres.</p>",
